PURPOSE OF THE DOCUMENT:
The purpose of this document is to outline the standardised procedures needed in seting up a virtual linux server for application testing.
This document ensures that the virtual linux server is configured properly and securedly to support documentation and testing.

AUDIENCE:
The audience of this doccument are Software Developers, Quality and Assurance Testers, System and IT Administrator, DevOps Engineers and Students

SCOPE:
The scopes covered by this SOP are to be applied when:
1. A new testing environment is required
2. Testing or troubleshooting a created web application
The objectives of this SOP are:
1. Creation of a virtual linux server
2. Installation of required web services
3. Configuration of networking and firewall rules
4. Validation of web applicaton testing environment

