PROCEDURE STEPS:
Step 1: Create the Virtual Machine
1. Open the virtualisation software(VirtualBox, VMware or Proxmox)
2. Select Create New Virtual Machine
3. Name it "webtest-server", choose the type to be Linux and the version Ubuntu LTS(64-bit)
4. Configure the system with 2 CPU cores, 4gb RAM and 20 gb NVMe SSD storage.
5. Attach the Ubuntu server ISO file
6. Set the network adapter to NAT or Bridged
7. Start the virtual Machine

Step 2: Install the Operating System
1. Select Install Ubuntu Server 
2. Choose preferred language and keyboard layout
3. Configure network to use DHCP
4. Set the hostname as "webtest-server"
5. Create the user account with a username and pasword of your choice
6. Select Install OpenSSH Server when prompted
7. After the installation is done, reboot the system and log in with your created credentials

Step 3: Update System and Configure Network
1. In the command line, use "sudo apt update" to update package repository
2. Use "sudo apt upgrade -y" to upgrade installed packages
3. Check your IP address with "ip a" and check your internet connectivity with "ping -c 4 google.com"

Step 4: Install Web Server
1. Install Apache wit "sudo apt install apachew -y"
2. Start Apache service with "sudo systemctl start apache2"
3. Enable Apache to start at boot with "sudo systemctl enable apache2"
4. Verify Apache status with "sudo systemctl status apache2"

Step 5: Install Database Server
1. Install MySQL with "sudo apt install mysql-server -y"
2. Secure MySQL installation wirh "sudo mysql_secure_installation"

Step 6: Install PHP and required Modules
1. Install PHP and it's requirements with "sudo apt install php libapache2-mod-php php-mysql -y"
2. Restart Apache with "sudo systemctl restart apache2"

Step 7: Configure Firewall
1. Allow SSH with "sudo ufw allow OpenSSH"
2. Allow Apache with "sudo ufw allow 'Apache'"
3. Enable firewall with "sudo ufw enable"

Step 8: Create Test Web Page
1. Create PHP test file with "sudo nano /var/www/html/info.php"
2. Add content:
"<?php
phpinfo();
?>"
3. Save and exit

Step 9: Verify Web Server
1. Open web browser on host machine
2. Enter the Linux server IP address "http://<server-ip-address>"
3. Test PHP page "http://<server-ip-address>/info.php"
4. If configured correctly the Apache default page would load and the PHP information page displays

